## 7. Regularization

When $p$ is large or features are correlated, plain OLS can **overfit**. Regularization adds a **penalty term** to the loss.

### 7.1 Ridge Regression (L2)

$$\hat{\boldsymbol{\beta}}_{\text{ridge}} = \arg\min_{\boldsymbol{\beta}} \left\{ \|\mathbf{y} - \mathbf{X}\boldsymbol{\beta}\|^2 + \lambda \|\boldsymbol{\beta}\|^2 \right\}$$

Closed-form solution:

$$\hat{\boldsymbol{\beta}}_{\text{ridge}} = (\mathbf{X}^\top \mathbf{X} + \lambda \mathbf{I})^{-1} \mathbf{X}^\top \mathbf{y}$$

- Shrinks all coefficients toward zero but **never sets them exactly to zero**.
- Stabilises the inversion when $\mathbf{X}^\top \mathbf{X}$ is near-singular.

### 7.2 Lasso Regression (L1)

$$\hat{\boldsymbol{\beta}}_{\text{lasso}} = \arg\min_{\boldsymbol{\beta}} \left\{ \|\mathbf{y} - \mathbf{X}\boldsymbol{\beta}\|^2 + \lambda \|\boldsymbol{\beta}\|_1 \right\}$$

- Produces **sparse solutions** — sets some $\hat{\beta}_j = 0$ exactly.
- Performs implicit **feature selection**.
- No closed form; solved via coordinate descent.

### 7.3 Elastic Net

Combines both penalties:

$$\hat{\boldsymbol{\beta}}_{\text{EN}} = \arg\min_{\boldsymbol{\beta}} \left\{ \|\mathbf{y} - \mathbf{X}\boldsymbol{\beta}\|^2 + \lambda_1 \|\boldsymbol{\beta}\|_1 + \lambda_2 \|\boldsymbol{\beta}\|^2 \right\}$$

Or equivalently with mixing parameter $\alpha \in [0,1]$:

$$\text{Penalty} = \lambda \left[ \alpha \|\boldsymbol{\beta}\|_1 + \frac{(1-\alpha)}{2} \|\boldsymbol{\beta}\|^2 \right]$$

### Regularization Path

```
|β|
 ▲
 │ OLS
 │ ●────────────────────────── β₁
 │    ╲
 │     ╲──────────────────────  β₂
 │          ╲─────────────────  β₃
 │               ╲──── 0        β₄  (Lasso: zeroed out)
 └──────────────────────────►
              λ →
    small λ              large λ
  (less reg)           (more reg)
```

