## 8. Logistic Regression (Linear Classifier)

For **binary classification** ($y \in \{0, 1\}$), we model the **log-odds**:

$$\log \frac{P(y=1 \mid \mathbf{x})}{P(y=0 \mid \mathbf{x})} = \boldsymbol{\beta}^\top \mathbf{x}$$

Applying the **sigmoid (logistic) function** $\sigma(z) = \frac{1}{1+e^{-z}}$:

$$P(y=1 \mid \mathbf{x}) = \sigma(\boldsymbol{\beta}^\top \mathbf{x}) = \frac{1}{1 + e^{-\boldsymbol{\beta}^\top \mathbf{x}}}$$

### Loss Function — Binary Cross-Entropy (Log-Loss)

$$\mathcal{L}(\boldsymbol{\beta}) = -\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n} \left[ y_i \log \hat{p}_i + (1 - y_i) \log(1 - \hat{p}_i) \right]$$

There is **no closed-form solution** — optimised with gradient descent or Newton-Raphson:

$$\boldsymbol{\beta}^{(t+1)} = \boldsymbol{\beta}^{(t)} - \eta \nabla_{\boldsymbol{\beta}} \mathcal{L}$$

where $\eta$ is the learning rate.

