### 10.4 Gradient Descent for Linear Regression

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant D as Data (X, y)
    participant M as Model (β)
    participant L as Loss Function
    participant G as Gradient ∇L

    D->>M: Initialise β randomly
    loop Until convergence
        M->>L: Compute ŷ = Xβ
        L->>L: Compute MSE = (1/n)||y - ŷ||²
        L->>G: Compute ∇β = -(2/n) Xᵀ(y - Xβ)
        G->>M: Update β ← β - η·∇β
    end
    M-->>D: Return optimal β̂
```

